metadata.name: Floatrest #154
metadata.description:
Floating forests over the endless sky, where birds, trees, plants, roots, rocks and waterfalls share an ecosystem full of life and emotion.

You can see some rain clouds in the sky and the sun shining under the raindrops.

The earth is moving, the blocks are falling, but the trees are strong in their roots.

Welcome to 'Floatrest'.

----

# Features

- 7 tree palettes
- 17 different background colors
- 10 different terrain colors
- clouds
- vines
- roots
- plants
- waterfall
- birds
- sun / moon
- night
- dark mode
- monochromatic
- 2 different aspect ratios (square & portrait)
- Press "p" on live mode to save in PNG

This artwork requires processing power and is intended for laptops and desktops primarily. It may take some time to render.

----

July 2022, gpitombo

metadata.name: Euphonic #1324
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moir√© effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

metadata.description:
More info: https://greweb.me/plots/509

'Wireframe' explores the realm of 3D noise mixed with various generative techniques. Many rare features and easter eggs are to discover.

metadata.name: Drifters #102
metadata.description:
In an undiscovered area, you've stumbled upon an unknown creature.
It looks weirdly haunting, and you're feeling a sense of unease.

You're wondering what it's doing.

It seems to move in patterns, and sometimes suddenly changes course.
Is it communicating?

(to whom?)

Setting aside your discomfort for a moment, you're realizing you could be seeing it wrong.
While the creature does look eerie and its motivations are unclear,
you realize every culture has its own appreciation of aesthetics,
and you can't help noticing there is a certain grace to this performance.

And it all makes sense.

You're witnessing uncharted explorations of elegance.

metadata.name: Mind scribbles #92
Tapestry #67
metadata.description:
Tapestry celebrates palettes and texture. It emphasizes the power of palettes by using them in a unique texture with infinite variations.

Tapestry has 136 very distinct palettes, each with it's own (not so secret) backstory.

The mint size of 747 was chosen because that is the expected number of mints required to get at least one of each palette. For anyone interested, this is called the coupon collector problem and has an accurate approximate solution of n * (ln(n) + .577216) + 0.5

Algorithm

The patterns and colors are generated by using parameterized Perlin noise, and a custom algorithm is used for the canvas-like texture. The canvas texture was especially satisfying since it is generated very fast by manipulating the z values with trigonometric functions. This allows Tapestry to render efficiently on any screen size (see the Responsive section below).

Attributes

Palette - each palette has an equal chance of being selected.
Amplitude - determines the overall turbulence in the pattern.
Vertical Variation - the variation in the vertical component of the pattern.
Horizontal Variation - the variation in the horizontal component of the pattern.
Noise Factor - the amount of noise the the overall pattern.
Color Variation - the variation in the color changes.

Rarities

The minting process will sort out the rarities. Since there are only 747 mints for 136 palettes, there will most certainly be some very rare palettes, probably a few with only one mint.

The other attributes produce billions of variations, virtually guaranteeing that each pattern will be entirely unique.

Responsive

Tapestry is responsive and will render on any screen size. Due to it's rendering speed, it's well suited for 4K or larger screens.

Notes

's' saves an image using the exact size of the current window so you can get an image in any resolution.

Since displays vary so widely and Tapestry will work on any any screen size, you can tweak the grain and brightness using the left/right arrow keys (grain), and up/down arrow keys (brightness). 'r' resets the values to the defaults.

metadata.name: Alleles #167
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

metadata.name: Beautiful Mind #40
metadata.description:
In the logical completion of tasks, thought, order and action play a very basic, basic and sensitive role if applied in the same way.
For every operation and the most difficult tasks, these three phenomena should be used in the planning stage correctly and logically, so that the task will be completed at the right time and reach the right result.
The creative mind must determine if each of these three phenomena plays its role in the work before initiating any action, especially in basic and infrastructure works (such as social and economic planning or long-term educational and training programs).
Thinking before taking any action is one of the most fundamental underlying issues of taking any action in order to design and plan a logical and reasonable framework.
It is generally understood that thoughts, orders, and actions work together, for example, order only becomes possible when thought about a phenomenon begins, and gradually, the effects become evident.

The purpose of this code is to force minds to be creative.
